Rivalry clash is still going on between supporters of the two governorship contenders of APC in Cross River state, even as President Muhammadu Buhari made his way into the UJ Esuene Stadium for his presidential rally on Wednesday. Large numbers of supporters of Senator John Owan-Enoh and those of Minister of Niger Delta Usani Usani used planks and other weapons to attack each other. Our correspondent reports that at least two supporters of the Owan-Enoh were fatally injured in the ensuing imbroglio.  Details later… 3-hour protest for Usani locks Calabar APC gov’ship hopeful courts Olumba in C/River C/River: Gov’ship hopeful seeks reconciliation with minister